## Monorepo Structure
```
meriter-nextjs/
├── api/                          # Backend package (@meriter/api)
├── web/                          # Frontend package (@meriter/web)
├── libs/shared-types/            # Shared types package
├── package.json                  # Root package (monorepo)
└── pnpm-workspace.yaml           # pnpm workspace config
```

Notes:
- Root `pnpm-workspace.yaml` lists workspace packages `api`, `web`, and `libs/shared-types`.
- `web/pnpm-workspace.yaml` exists but does not duplicate the root workspace package list; it carries pnpm-only settings (e.g. `ignoredBuiltDependencies` for `mongodb-memory-server` and `sharp`).

## Backend Structure (api/)
```
api/apps/meriter/src/
├── domain/                       # Domain layer
│   ├── models/[entity]/          # Mongoose schemas (schemas only; IO in infrastructure)
│   ├── services/                 # Business services (+ factors/)
│   ├── ports/                    # Persistence + PermissionGatesPort interfaces
│   ├── aggregates/               # Domain entities
│   ├── events/                   # Domain events + event bus
│   └── value-objects/
├── application/                  # Application layer
│   ├── use-cases/[domain]/       # Orchestration (~60 use cases)
│   ├── application.module.ts
│   └── _bootstrap.ts             # Optional Nest registration (factories used from routers today)
├── adapters/                     # Adapter layer (partial; trpc/ still primary mount)
│   ├── mappers/, presenters/, enrichment/, resolvers/, rest/, trpc/
│   └── adapters.module.ts
├── infrastructure/               # Infrastructure layer
│   ├── persistence/              # Port adapters + mappers
│   ├── auth/                     # CookieManager, session
│   ├── cron/
│   └── telegram/
├── trpc/                         # Primary tRPC mount (thin routers)
│   ├── routers/[entity].router.ts
│   └── context.ts
├── api-v1/                       # REST (auth, config, legacy uploads)
├── common/                       # Shared backend utilities (helpers, services, interfaces, decorators, interceptors, filters, pipes, exceptions, validation, database)
│   └── schemas/                  # Backend-only Zod schemas (small set; e.g. `pagination.schema.ts`)
├── config/                       # NestJS runtime configuration (e.g. `configuration.ts`)
├── decorators/                   # Top-level Nest param decorators (e.g. `user.decorator.ts`; permission/Zod decorators also live under `common/decorators/`)
├── telegram/                     # Telegram integration
├── tg-bots/                      # Telegram bot module and services
├── updates-conductors/           # Update conductor subsystem
├── migrations/                   # One-off migration scripts
├── seed-data/                    # Dev/demo seed snapshots, loaders, TSV/JSON helpers
├── i18n/                         # Backend locale message maps
├── meriter.module.ts             # Root Nest module composition
├── meriter.controller.ts         # Root controller
├── meriter.service.ts            # Root app service
├── config.ts                     # App URL from `DOMAIN`, bot env constants, Telegram message templates
├── permission.guard.ts           # Permission guard
├── user.guard.ts                 # Authenticated user guard
└── main.ts                       # App entry point
```

Notes:
- `domain/models/` includes auth-related schemas (e.g. passkey challenge schema)
- Domain contains dedicated background modules/services (e.g. quota reset and post-closing cron modules)
- `trpc/types.ts` re-exports type-only `AppRouter` from `trpc/router.ts` for the frontend (see Common Mistakes). The web app imports that type via a relative path in `web/src/lib/trpc/client.ts` (still type-only).
- `trpc/router.ts` `appRouter` namespaces: `users`, `communities`, `auth`, `config`, `publications`, `comments`, `votes`, `polls`, `wallets`, `notifications`, `search`, `uploads`, `favorites`, `categories`, `about`, `tappalka`, `investments`, `teams`, `platformSettings`, `project`, `ticket`, `platformDev`, `meritTransfer`.
- Sub-router file/export names may differ from the `appRouter` key (e.g. `investmentRouter` from `investment.router.ts` is mounted as `investments`).
- Migration and maintenance scripts also live under `api/scripts/` (outside `api/apps/meriter/src/`); some are wired from `api/package.json` scripts.

### Adding New Backend Feature

1. Add/update schema in `domain/models/[entity]/`
2. Add **`domain/ports/[entity].persistence.port.ts`** + **`infrastructure/persistence/[entity].persistence.adapter.ts`** if new persistence entity
3. Implement business rules in `domain/services/`; **orchestration** in **`application/use-cases/[domain]/[action].use-case.ts`**
4. Register port in `infrastructure/persistence/persistence.module.ts` and providers in `domain.module.ts`
5. Expose via **thin** tRPC router: validate → `createXUseCase(ctx).execute(...)` → map response
6. **Never** import logic from other routers (Zone 9)
7. REST only for auth/bootstrap/config narrow paths; no new REST business endpoints
8. Attach `ResourcePermissions` via `PermissionRuleEngine` + presenter
9. Shared contracts in `libs/shared-types/src/` when cross-package

## Frontend Structure (web/)
```
web/src/
├── app/                          # 🔵 Next.js App Router
│   ├── meriter/                  # Main app routes
│   ├── tests/                    # Test/demo routes
│   ├── **/route.ts               # App Router route handlers (few; e.g. `app/auth/link/[token]/route.ts`, `app/a/[token]/route.ts`)
│   ├── layout.tsx                # Root layout
│   └── page.tsx                  # Home page
├── components/                   # 🟢 UI Components
│   ├── atoms/                    # Smallest UI primitives (design-system pieces)
│   ├── ui/                       # Base UI (buttons, inputs)
│   ├── molecules/                # Composite UI pieces
│   ├── organisms/                # Complex feature blocks
│   ├── templates/                # Page/layout templates
│   ├── settings/                 # Settings-related components
│   └── providers/                # React provider wrappers/components
├── features/                     # 🟡 Feature modules
├── hooks/                        # Custom React hooks (most tRPC-related hooks live under hooks/api/)
├── stores/                       # Zustand stores
├── contexts/                     # React contexts
├── lib/                          # Utilities: trpc/, api/, routing/, constants/, i18n/, community/, comments/, utils/, ...
├── i18n/                         # i18n request/config layer
├── config/                       # Runtime frontend config
├── providers/                    # Provider components
├── shared/                       # Shared UI/lib/hooks/stores/types
├── types/                        # TypeScript types
├── generated/                    # Auto-generated build metadata
└── __tests__/                    # Frontend tests (see note below)
```

Notes:
- `web/tsconfig.json` path aliases: `@/*`, `@app/*`, `@features/*`, `@shared/*`, `@types/*`, `@lib/*` (→ `shared/lib/*`), `@meriter/shared-types`, `@config/*`, `@styles/*`.
- `web/tsconfig.json` excludes `**/__tests__/**` and `**/*.test.*` / `**/*.spec.*` from compilation; test files may still live under those paths.

### Adding New Frontend Feature
1. Prefer **`features/[domain]/`** for domain-scoped UI (hooks, forms, types); export public API via `index.ts` only — no cross-feature internal imports
2. Keep `app/meriter/**/page.tsx` as thin shells delegating to `*Client.tsx` or feature modules
3. Shared primitives in `components/atoms|molecules|ui/`; cross-feature chrome in `components/organisms/`
4. Server data via tRPC + TanStack Query; types from `@meriter/shared-types` — never import `api/apps/meriter/src/**`
5. Merit display: use `web/src/lib/utils/currency.ts`; must match backend one-decimal rounding (inv-26)
6. Product copy: «Заслуги» only; Obsidian Nocturne tokens — @design-system.mdc

## Shared Types (libs/shared-types/)
```
libs/shared-types/src/
├── base-schemas.ts               # Base Zod primitives
├── schemas.ts                    # Complex DTOs
├── taxonomy.ts                   # Shared taxonomy enums/lists
├── tappalka.ts                   # Shared tappalka-specific schemas
├── value-rubricator.ts           # Value rubricator types/helpers
├── decree809-tag-remap.ts        # Decree809 tag remap
└── index.ts                      # Public exports
```

### When to Use Shared Types
✅ Type is used in BOTH frontend and backend
✅ Type is part of API contract
❌ Type is backend-only validation → use `api/apps/meriter/src/common/schemas/`
❌ Type is frontend-only UI state → use `web/src/types/`

## Key Patterns

### Service Layer (Backend)
```typescript
// domain/services/[entity].service.ts
@Injectable()
export class EntityService {
  constructor(
    @InjectModel(Entity.name) private model: Model<Entity>,
    private otherService: OtherService,
  ) {}

  async create(dto: CreateEntityDto): Promise<Entity> {
    // Business logic here
  }
}
```

### tRPC Router (Backend)
```typescript
// trpc/routers/[entity].router.ts
export const entityRouter = router({
  getById: protectedProcedure
    .input(z.object({ id: z.string() }))
    .query(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      return ctx.entityService.getById(input.id);
    }),
});
```

### Component Pattern (Frontend)
```typescript
// components/[feature]/FeatureCard.tsx
interface FeatureCardProps {
  data: FeatureData;
  onAction?: () => void;
}

export function FeatureCard({ data, onAction }: FeatureCardProps) {
  // Component logic
}
```

