## Canonical enrichment path (API responses)

1. Load domain entities → 2. Batch fetch users/communities (`UserEnrichmentService`) → 3. `EntityMappers.map*ToApi` → 4. Router post-processing (transitional Mongo-only fields) → 5. `PermissionRuleEngine` allow/deny (via `PermissionGatesPort` Phase 3+) → 6. `permissions.presenter` → `ResourcePermissions` + i18n keys only → 7. Return shared-types DTO.

## OD-3 permissions split (pending product sign-off)

- **Invariant enforcer:** `PermissionRuleEngine` owns all allow/deny gates (Phase 5 migration from `permissions-helper`)
- **Presenter only:** `permissions.presenter` assembles booleans + i18n disabled-reason keys (`voteDisabled.*`, etc.)
- **Phase 3 interim:** engine stub methods delegate to `PermissionGatesPort`; adapter is sole `permissions-helper` importer
- **Sign-off gate:** `.index/architecture/od3-matrix-signed.yaml` must be product-signed before Phase 5 permissions merge

## Common Mistakes

❌ Importing backend runtime code from `api/` in `web/`
✅ Type-only import bridge: `api/apps/meriter/src/trpc/types.ts` re-exports `AppRouter` from `./router`. The web tRPC client imports it from there via a relative path (`web/src/lib/trpc/client.ts`).
❌ Duplicating types instead of using shared-types (especially `ResourcePermissions` — use `libs/shared-types` only)
❌ Domain service importing `trpc/helpers` or `api-v1/*`
❌ Cross-router imports (Zone 9) — use a shared use case instead
❌ `PermissionRuleEngine` importing `permissions-helper` — use `PermissionGatesPort`
❌ Inline `notificationService.createNotification` in domain services — domain event → `NotificationHandlersService`
❌ Adding orchestration god-methods in routers — extract to `application/use-cases/`
❌ `@InjectModel` in new domain services — add a persistence port + adapter
❌ Putting reusable shared components only in `app/` (prefer `features/`, `components/`, or `shared/components`)
